Three children from the same family have drowned in a dam in Mukinyai village in Molo.
Area Assistant Chief Zack Munari said the incident happened at around 4pm Saturday when the children were playing near a quarry.
He said the children were playing near the quarry which was flooded following heavy rains that pounded in the area recently. Mr Munari added that they all drowned as they tried to rescue each other.



