The assistant chief identified the children as Michael Kiritu, 8, Victor Kaniaru, 11, and Grace Wairimu, 15, â€” all pupils at the nearby Mukinyai Primary School.
He said the second child drowned as he tried to rescue his younger brother before their elder sister also drowned as she rushed to rescue her brothers.
Bodies retrieved
The incident has left locals in shock.
The administrator said local divers retrieved the bodies of the three from the dam at around 6pm.



